postcontent: This pistol is new, bought and never fired. It is 7 months old. I bought two at the time and I love these guns. Say what you may about Canik but these guns are unbelievably smooth and fast and accurate shooters right out of the box. As well built as any of my Glocks. Easy take down for cleaning. The pistol comes with all the original factory stuff except holster. I am keeping it for my other one. I have to date 5000+ rounds through my OD Canik and the only issue I have is heavy slide wear on barrel. I promise you this. Try one and you will see how amazing they are. The FDE is a favorite color of mine. This one is very different then others I have. It is the 9x19mm and holds 18+1 and comes with 2 mags. Again this pistol is new and unshot. No flaws or scratches anywhere. I am looking for a FDE color first to trade for in a SUB compact. 9mm preferred or a .45 XDs is fine. Please note this. I am NOT trading a new gun for a used one. Don’t even bother offering. I am NOT selling, I don’t need your money. Laugh if you will but there are guys out there just like me that buy two and three guns at a time to play with and collect and shoot. I like to trade every now and then for a current need or whim. I don’t need or have to trade it at all. After 45 years of collecting and shooting I am in it for fun now. I will look at all offers of NEW gun trades. Pistol for Pistol, face to face, written bill of trade and ID ‘s on both parties. I am a current CWP holder and very proud of it. I am NOT wanting any .22, .40, .38/357 stuff. I have a safe full of those. I love Bird head revolvers in the 3.75” length fron Ruger, Cimmeron, Uberti, etc. .45ACP but will consider a .357, .45 LC, .44. I like Glocks, XDs, M&P in FDE only, and the only .22 WMR is the Keltec PMR 30 in any color but black. If you have a compact to offer I will look at it. Please send pictures with the trade offer of you want a response from me. You see my gun so let me see yours. I am in Winfield, Kansas. If this ad is still up it is still for trade only. Trade value depends on where you shop. $375-$450 is where they are right now and the more people find out how great they are. It will only go up.

postcontent: This is an R-Guns imported Russian WWII PU Sniper.  The R-Guns imported snipers are the only ones that have been verified as legimate snipers (look if up!).  This one has all matching ORIGINAL stamped serial numbers including the prefixes.  It's a 1944 Izhevsk.  Still retains the original wartime stock with half liners as appropriate and deep, sharp, stock cartouches.  Scope is original wartime and was originally a SVT40 scope which was overhauled and then used with PUs as evident by the can design and "CB" marking on the turret- this was a common wartime practice.  Everything works perfectly as it should and glass is clear.  Very nice muzzle, bore, and nice light and crisp trigger.  And since it's an R-Guns import you also get the very tiny import marking. Comes with the canvas scope cover and leather lens covers.  If you're looking for a verified legit PU sniper I doubt you'll find a nicer example.
